ygData.messageBody:
I am 47, but pass for 35 easily. I am a mother, spec. ed.
compliance monitor, computer builder/fixer/networker, substitute
teacher, nutritional consultant, editor, graphic artist and
webmistress. (I think I forgot something!)

Don't major in computers, per se. That's like majoring in
screwdrivers. Pick an application for your tool. I had
programming back in 1977 and HATED it. Then in '93, I discovered
the Internet and fell instantly in love. A library in your house!
I started building and upgrading then. People say that when I am
the room, computers behave. They can sense fear and they know I
will rip their guts out!


____I am a computer nerdie female but look like a house wife. I'm
____returning to college next month or this month... haven't
decided. I did
____"Microcomputer Operations" but returning for "Computer
Programming".
____Beverly---
